[1] FAO: situation update
Date: Thu 20 Jun 2019
Source: UN Food & Agriculture Organisation (FAO)/EMPRES (FAO Emergency Prevention System) [abridged, edited]
[The document will become electronically available on Fri 21 Jun 2019 at http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/programmes/en/empres/ASF/Situation_update.html.]


Situation update for the period 14 to 20 Jun 2019 [The next update will be issued on 27 Jun 2019].
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lao People's Democratic Republic:
The Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry confirmed the occurrence of the 1st ASF outbreak in Toumian [Toomlarn] district, Salavan province on 20 Jun 2019.

Democratic People's Republic of Korea:
The Ministry of Agriculture confirmed the occurrence of the 1st ASF outbreak in Chagang province on 23 May 2019.
[see African swine fever - Asia (48): North Korea (CH) domestic, 1st rep, OIE 20190530.6494781. No new outbreaks reported during the past week]

China:
Since the China Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs (MARA) confirmed its 1st ASF outbreak in Liaoning province on 3 Aug 2018, a total of 139 ASF outbreaks have been detected in 32 provinces/autonomous regions/municipalities. Around 1 133 000 pigs have been culled in an effort to halt further spread. [No new outbreaks have been reported during the past week].

Taiwan:
A dead pig found on Erdan Island beach, Lieyu township (Lesser Kinmen), Kinmen county, Taiwan province on 14 Jun 2019 and tested positive for ASF virus by PCR. The genomic sequence analysis showed 100% identity with the ASF virus reported in other parts of China.

Mongolia:
Since its 1st report on 15 Jan 2019, 11 outbreaks in 6 provinces and in Ulaanbaatar have been reported, involving 105 farms/households. More than 3115 pigs -- more than 10% of the total pig population in Mongolia -- have died/been destroyed due to the ASF outbreaks. [No new outbreaks reported during the past week].

Viet Nam:
Since the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development (MARD) confirmed its 1st ASF outbreak on 19 Feb 2019, a total of 58 provinces/cities reported outbreaks, more than 2.6 million pigs have been culled. [During the past week, new outbreaks were reported from the provinces Long An and Phu Yen].

Cambodia:
Since the Ministry of Agriculture Forestry and Fisheries confirmed its 1st ASF outbreak in Som Kaninh village, Som Thom commune, O Ya Dav district, Ratanakiri province on 2 Apr 2019, more than 2400 pigs have died or been culled. [No new outbreaks reported during the past week].

New actions undertaken during the week
--------------------------------------
Viet Nam:
The Prime Minister released a Directive (no. 42 / NQ-CP, 18 Jun 2019) on Government decision regarding the prevention and control of ASF epidemic, which includes:
- support households, small, and medium-sized enterprises keeping grandparent pigs with VND 500 000/pig (approx. USD 21 USD/pig);
- support pig raising farmers and enterprises whose pigs are destroyed on the basis of price and pig raising costs suitable for each type of pig; higher support levels for sows and boars;
- support small and medium enterprises but not exceeding 30% of losses due to epidemics.

[No new actions reported from the other ASF-infected Asian countries during the past week].

--
Communicated by:
Juan Lubroth, DVM, PhD, ACVPM
Chief Veterinary Officer
Animal Health Service C-532
Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
Rome, Italy

